equation were two-x minus one

00:01:09.159 --> 00:01:10.819
is equal to the negative

00:01:10.819 --> 00:01:15.463
of the square root of eight minus x.

00:01:15.463 --> 00:01:17.959
Because if you squared both sides of this,

00:01:17.959 --> 00:01:19.642
you would also get,

00:01:19.642 --> 00:01:21.314
you would also get that right over there,

00:01:21.314 --> 00:01:25.036
because a negative squared
would be equal to a positive.

00:01:25.036 --> 00:01:27.293
So, when we're finding a solution to this,

00:01:27.293 --> 00:01:28.616
we need to test our solution

00:01:28.616 --> 00:01:30.032
to make sure it's truly the solution

00:01:30.032 --> 00:01:32.319
to this first yellow equation here,

00:01:32.319 --> 00:01:34.920
